<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section" id="faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="tag">Got Questions?</span>
      <h2>Frequently Asked <span class="gradient-text">Questions</span></h2>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-wrap" id="faqWrap">
      <div class="faq-item glass">
        <div class="faq-question">How do I report a lost item? <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Click "Report Lost Item" on the homepage, fill in your details and item description, and submit. You'll get updates as soon as a match is found.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item glass">
        <div class="faq-question">How is my claim verified? <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Claims go through OTP verification, Student ID confirmation, or security questions before an item is released to ensure it reaches the rightful owner.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item glass">
        <div class="faq-question">Is there a reward for returning items? <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>While rewards aren't mandatory, finders are recognized on their profile and can receive appreciation points redeemable for campus perks.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item glass">
        <div class="faq-question">What happens if no one claims a found item? <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Unclaimed items are held for 60 days, after which they're handed over to the campus administration office per policy.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item glass">
        <div class="faq-question">Is my personal information kept private? <i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i></div>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. Contact details are only shared between matched parties after claim verification is approved, in line with our Privacy Policy.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

